# Slopcast — Cursor Rules (Multi-Agent System)

## Project Conventions
Follow all conventions in `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root.

## Agent Roles
This project uses a multi-agent development system defined in `.agents/`.

### Acting as Supervisor
When asked to act as the supervisor (or when the user says "supervisor mode"):
- Read and follow `.agents/roles/supervisor.md`
- Read `.agents/workflows/feature-pipeline.md` for the full pipeline
- Decompose requests into tasks, create worktrees, coordinate implementation

### Acting as Implementer
When asked to implement a task (or when working in a `.worktrees/` directory):
- Read and follow `.agents/roles/implementer.md`
- Read existing code patterns before writing new code
- Run self-checks before committing: `npm run typecheck && npm test && npm run build`
- Stay within the scope of your assigned task

### Acting as Validator
When asked to validate (or when the user says "validate mode"):
- Read and follow `.agents/roles/validator.md`
- Run: `bash .agents/validation/gate.sh`
- Do NOT modify any code — report results only

## Worktree Operations
See `.agents/workflows/worktree-lifecycle.md` for create/work/validate/merge/cleanup.

```bash
# Create worktree
git worktree add -b agent/{slug} .worktrees/{slug} main
cd .worktrees/{slug} && npm install

# Validate
bash .agents/validation/gate.sh

# Merge (from repo root)
git checkout main && git merge --no-ff agent/{slug}

# Cleanup
git worktree remove .worktrees/{slug} && git branch -d agent/{slug}
```

## Key Files
- `src/types.ts` — All TypeScript interfaces
- `src/constants.ts` — Mock data and defaults
- `src/utils/economics.ts` — Pure economics calculations (well-tested)
- `src/hooks/useSlopcastWorkspace.ts` — Main workspace state hook
- `src/pages/SlopcastPage.tsx` — Main page (pure JSX)
